_506076726393186_5572840046471413760_n.png?_nc_cat=103&ccb=1-7&_nc_sid=6e7a0a&_nc_ohc=dU9N5rLk6PMQ7kNvgFKjOCI&_nc_zt=3&_nc_ht=scontent-sjc3-1.oculuscdn.com&oh=00_AYDGXIJkCUEpPCKuSQ_VC4TIgMunXiSdVT1ZiG-4ugQDzA&oe=67260A63"}], "video_trailer": null, "video_trailer_thumbnail": null, "display_name": "PaperLander Demo", "keywords": ["paper", "rocket", "gravity", "cute", "free"], "long_description": "PaperLander is a fragile rocket made out of - you guessed it - paper. He lives in PaperGalaxy, a low gravitational fantasy world far far away, made mostly out of paper too.\n\nBut now the Galaxy is in danger. A Space Storm is approaching and threatens to tear it apart. Only one thing can stop the Storm: The Great Anti-Storm Ion Cannon! But it works only with Proto-Stars. And Proto-Stars are scattered in the Galaxy, across its many Sectors. These Sectors are connected by a network of teleporters that activate upon landing. PaperLander's mission is to find and collect those Stars, pass through the Sectors using the teleporters and bring them to the Anti-Storm Ion Cannon in time to save the Galaxy!\n\nBuild your own PaperLander here: http://thiswayupgames.com/PaperLanderModel.pdf\n\n--------------------------------\nPlease note that this demo is not compatible with Oculus Go", "short_description": "PaperLander is a fragile rocket made out of - you guessed it - paper. He lives in PaperGalaxy, a low gravitational fantasy world far far away, made mostly out of paper too.\n\nBuild your own PaperLander here: http://thiswayupgames.com/PaperLanderModel.pdf\n\nBut now the Galaxy is in danger. A Space Storm is approaching and threatens to tear it apart. Only one thing can stop the Storm: The Great Anti-Storm Ion Cannon! But it works only with Proto-Stars, which are scattered in the Galaxy."}]}, "developer_name": null, "developer_privacy_policy_url": "http://thiswayupgames.com/privacy.html", "developer_terms_of_service_url": "http://thiswayupgames.com/terms.html", "publisher_name": "Self 